# DevSecOps Tutorial

This project demonstrates the integration of security into the DevOps lifecycle using various tools and practices. The goal is to build, test, and deploy a secure web application.

## Technologies Used

- Node.js
- React
- Docker
- Kubernetes
- Jenkins
- SonarQube
- OWASP ZAP
- Snyk
- Prometheus & Grafana
- ELK Stacks

## Backend

To run the backend server:

```bash
cd backend
node server.js


## Frontend

To run the frontend application:

```bash
cd frontend
npm start

## CI/CD Pipeline

This project uses GitHub Actions for continuous integration.

The pipeline is defined in `.github/workflows/ci.yml` and runs on every push and pull request to the `main` branch.

## Dockerization

To build and run the Docker images:

```bash
# Backend
cd backend
docker build -t backend:latest .
docker run -p 3000:3000 backend:latest

# Frontend
cd frontend
docker build -t frontend:latest .
docker run -p 3000:3000 frontend:latest
